profile_positions.description:
Developing Technology Due Diligence capabilities and propositions with Deloitte Value Creation Services.

The capabilities consist of:
- IT DD evaluations;
- Product & Platform Software DD;
- Cyber security DD;
- Separation/carve-out Technology evaluations and support.

Daily activities include the following:
- Conducting Technology Due Diligence and pre-deal IT M&A assessments;
- Analyzing relevant industry developments and reviewing business and technology strategies;
- Mapping current and end-state technology, business models and architecture;
- Assessing technology stacks, core processes and technology spend and reviewing investment plans;
- Developing and pitching deal-related technology insights to clients;
- Shaping and further developing a very successful proposition.

As an IT Risk and Controls Analyst, I am responsible for supporting process owners throughout to document, maintain & monitor internal controls in line with our risk appetite and to maintain the quality of our processes.

My key areas of responsibility include, but not limited to:
• Conducting design and operational testing of internal controls within agreed timescales;
• Coordination with process owners regarding control documentation, testing, evaluation, and necessary remediation;
• Identification of control weaknesses and supporting of the control team to influence process owners to implement agreed changes in a timely and effective manner;
• Supporting the team to identify ways to increase their business impact and improve the team’s product(s) and ways of working;
• Supporting audit activities and helping to close any controls deficiencies identified.

The above mentioned activities help me building and supporting my professional knowledge of regulations like SOx, PCI DSS, GDPR and various consumer and competition compliance regulations, as well as frameworks like ERM and COBIT 2019. Moreover, the nature of Booking.com allows me gaining knowledge on how the risk management works in DevOps environment and get acquainted working with tools such as Puppet, Git, Docker and Kubernetes.
